{"id": "duc04-testb-18:0#1", "contents": "The reaction to Livingston's announcement was mixed, with some Republicans welcoming the news and others expressing disappointment. Rep. Tom DeLay of Texas, the majority whip, praised Livingston's decision, saying it was about \"honor and decency and integrity and the truth.\" However, Democrats were critical of the move, with Rep. Jerrold Nadler of New York calling it a \"surrender to a developing sexual McCarthyism.\" The White House also weighed in, with press secretary Joe Lockhart stating that President Clinton was \"disappointed\" by the news and urging Livingston to reconsider his decision."}
